A woman and her two grey parrots were killed in an alleged arson attack on their third floor flat on Everham Road in Westham, Phoenix, KwaZulu-Natal, on Monday morning. Spokesperson for the Reaction Unit South Africa, (RUSA) Prem Balram, said they received a call requesting assistance after residents saw smoke coming from one of the flats. “On arrival, fire fighters were in the process of entering the building. While extinguishing the blaze, firemen discovered the body of a female. Two African Grey Parrots were also killed,” said Balram. He said according to neighbours, the woman lived in the apartment with her 12-year-old son and boyfriend. Police were yet to comment.